<body>
    <h1>Artefact Completion and Blast Radius</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-1.Metadata">1. Metadata<=
/h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Feature name:</strong> Artefact Completion and Blast Radius</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>Module(s):</strong> DevQL watcher, DevQL ingestion, DevQL query =
pipeline</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Tech lead:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Draft</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Target release:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Related Feature spec brief:</strong> Artefact and dependency gra=
ph completion for TS/JS + Rust</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Related Jira epic (if applicable):</strong> TBD</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-2.Overview">2. Overview</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Problemstatement">Problem statem=
ent</h3>
<p>DevQL currently needs a complete and trustworthy symbol and dependency g=
raph in order to support blast-radius analysis, reverse dependency queries =
(<code>who depends on me</code>), and precise local developer feedback duri=
ng editing.</p>
<p>This feature is no longer only about committed ingest. DevQL now operate=
s across two complementary state models:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Current workspace state</strong> in <code>artefacts_current</cod=
e> and <code>artefact_edges_current</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Historical committed state</strong> in <code>artefacts</code> an=
d <code>artefact_edges</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Local file changes can be indexed into the current tables immediately as=
 temporary revisions. Later, <code>bitloops devql ingest</code> promotes ma=
tching temporary current rows to committed current rows when the blob in th=
e temporary revision matches <code>HEAD</code>, and persists committed hist=
orical rows for point-in-time queries.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Goals">Goals</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Extract artefacts with tree-sitter only for TS/JS and Rust.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Emit dependency edges for <code>imports</code>, <code>calls</code>, <cod=
e>references</code>, <code>extends</code>, <code>implements</code>, and <co=
de>exports</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Support reverse dependency analysis via <code>deps(direction:"in")</code=
>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Maintain <strong>live current-state indexing</strong> for local workspac=
e changes in <code>artefacts_current</code> and <code>artefact_edges_curren=
t</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Promote temporary current rows to committed current rows during <code>de=
vql ingest</code> when <code>HEAD</code> matches the temporary blob.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>Persist committed historical rows in <code>artefacts</code> and <code>ar=
tefact_edges</code> for <code>asOf(commit/ref)</code> queries.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Keep symbol identity stable across formatting changes and line moves whe=
n semantics are unchanged.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Keep re-ingestion idempotent for unchanged code.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Use canonical kinds only for cross-language abstractions; keep language-=
specific constructs in <code>language_kind</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Success metric: on curated TS/JS + Rust fixtures, expected artefacts and=
 edges are present and stable across repeated ingest runs and local edit cy=
cles.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Non-goals">Non-goals</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Parse-failure persistence/retry mechanism</p></li>
<li>
<p>Property/field artefacts in V1</p></li>
<li>
<p>Deep semantic/type inference beyond AST-level extraction</p></li>
<li>
<p>Recomputing semantic features, embeddings, and clone edges on every file=
 save</p></li>
<li>
<p>Full live-backend parity across every relational provider in this featur=
e scope</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Openquestions">Open questions</h=
3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>ID</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Decision topic</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Context</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Options considered</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Implications</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Decision</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>D1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Variable scope</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Example: <code>export const API_URL =3D ...</code> vs <code>const intern=
alCacheKey =3D ...</code> at file top-level. Should both be indexed as <cod=
e>variable</code>?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All top-level / Exported only</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All top-level gives better internal blast radius; exported-only reduces =
graph noise and token output.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Only exported</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Proposed</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>D2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Live relational backend parity</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Current live indexing behavior is implemented around current-state table=
s and workspace revisions; backend parity may differ by provider.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SQLite-first / Full provider parity</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SQLite-first is pragmatic; full parity reduces behavior drift between en=
vironments.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TBD</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Open</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>D3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Live enrichment boundary</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Current workspace indexing updates structural artefacts/edges immediatel=
y, while semantic features, embeddings, and clone edges are refreshed durin=
g ingest.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Structural-only live updates / Full live enrichment</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Structural-only is cheaper and simpler; full live enrichment gives stron=
ger real-time answers but costs more.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Structural-only in V1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Proposed</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-3.Scope">3. Scope</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Inscope">In scope</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Tree-sitter-only artefact extraction for TS/JS and Rust</p></li>
<li>
<p>Canonical artefact normalization with language-specific <code>language_k=
ind</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>V1 edges: <code>imports</code>, <code>calls</code>, <code>references</co=
de>, <code>extends</code>, <code>implements</code>, <code>exports</code></p=
></li>
<li>
<p><code>deps(...)</code> query support with <code>kind</code>, <code>direc=
tion</code>, and <code>include_unresolved</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Watcher-driven local updates to <code>artefacts_current</code> and <code=
>artefact_edges_current</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Temporary revision tracking for workspace changes</p></li>
<li>
<p>Promotion of matching temporary current rows to committed current rows d=
uring <code>devql ingest</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Historical persistence in <code>artefacts</code> and <code>artefact_edge=
s</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Query routing between current state, temporary revisions, and historical=
 committed state</p></li>
<li>
<p>Deterministic upsert and re-ingest behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Outofscope">Out of scope</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Parse-failure persistence and retry command flow in V1</p></li>
<li>
<p>Property/field artefacts</p></li>
<li>
<p>Full interprocedural/type-checker-level symbol resolution</p></li>
<li>
<p>Refreshing semantic features, embeddings, and clone edges on every works=
pace save</p></li>
<li>
<p>Redesign of watcher lifecycle/process architecture</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-4.Assumptions&amp;constraints">4=
. Assumptions &amp; constraints</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Extraction uses tree-sitter parsers for TS/JS and Rust.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Live structural indexing writes to <code>artefacts_current</code> and <c=
ode>artefact_edges_current</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Historical committed state is stored in <code>artefacts</code> and <code=
>artefact_edges</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>file_state</code> is the commit/path/blob bridge used for historic=
al path resolution.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Semantic features, embeddings, and clone edges are refreshed by <code>de=
vql ingest</code>, not by each local edit.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Rust <code>trait</code> is normalized to canonical <code>interface</code=
>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Language-specific constructs that are not cross-language abstractions do=
 not get canonical kinds in V1.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Current live indexing should be described as structural current-state in=
dexing, not full DevQL enrichment.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-5.Userstories">5. User stories</=
h2>
<p><strong>US1 - Analyze outgoing dependencies</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to list what a symbol imports/calls/references <br>
So that I can understand what it depends on</p>
<p><strong>US2 - Analyze incoming dependencies (blast radius)</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to find who depends on a symbol <br>
So that I can estimate change impact before editing or merging</p>
<p><strong>US3 - See local workspace impact before commit</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want local edits to update current DevQL state <br>
So that blast-radius analysis reflects what is currently in my workspace</p=
>
<p><strong>US4 - Query historical committed state</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to query artefacts and dependencies at a commit or ref <br>
So that I can compare behavior across revisions</p>
<p><strong>US5 - Preserve symbol continuity across non-semantic edits</stro=
ng> <br>
As a platform engineer <br>
I want symbol identity to remain stable across line moves and formatting-on=
ly edits <br>
So that analytics and lineage stay coherent</p>
<p><strong>US6 - Read symbols with low lookup cost</strong> <br>
As a CLI consumer <br>
I want a DB record for a symbol to be directly queryable <br>
So that lookups are efficient</p>
<p><strong>US7 - Get language-specific precision when needed</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to filter by <code>language_kind</code> for constructs like <code>im=
pl_item</code> or <code>struct_item</code> <br>
So that I retain fidelity without polluting canonical analytics</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-6.Functionalflows(Mermaid)">6. F=
unctional flows (Mermaid)</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-6.1High-levelflow">6.1 High-leve=
l flow</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">flowcha=
rt TD
    A["Workspace file change"] --&gt; B["Watcher batches changed paths"]
    B --&gt; C["Create temporary revision"]
    C --&gt; D["Upsert artefacts_current"]
    C --&gt; E["Upsert artefact_edges_current"]
    D --&gt; F["Default DevQL query or asOf(save:\"current\")"]
    E --&gt; F

    G["devql ingest"] --&gt; H["Process committed checkpoints"]
    G --&gt; I["Promote matching temporary current rows when HEAD blob matc=
hes"]
    H --&gt; J["Upsert artefacts"]
    H --&gt; K["Upsert artefact_edges"]
    G --&gt; L["Refresh semantic features / embeddings / clone edges"]
    J --&gt; M["Historical query asOf(commit/ref)"]
    K --&gt; M
    I --&gt; F</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-6.2Sequencediagram">6.2 Sequence=
 diagram</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">sequenc=
eDiagram
    participant DEV as Developer
    participant W as DevQL Watcher
    participant ING as DevQL Ingest
    participant DB as Relational Store
    participant Q as DevQL Query

    DEV-&gt;&gt;W: save file
    W-&gt;&gt;DB: write temporary revision metadata
    W-&gt;&gt;DB: upsert artefacts_current / artefact_edges_current
    DEV-&gt;&gt;Q: query without asOf(...)
    Q-&gt;&gt;DB: read current tables
    DB--&gt;&gt;Q: current workspace graph

    DEV-&gt;&gt;ING: bitloops devql ingest
    ING-&gt;&gt;DB: persist artefacts / artefact_edges
    ING-&gt;&gt;DB: promote matching temporary current rows
    ING-&gt;&gt;DB: refresh semantic features / embeddings / clone edges
    DEV-&gt;&gt;Q: query asOf(commit/ref)
    Q-&gt;&gt;DB: read historical tables
    DB--&gt;&gt;Q: committed historical graph</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-7.BDDscenarios(sourceoftruth)">7=
. BDD scenarios (source of truth)</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-7.1Happypaths">7.1 Happy paths</=
h3>
<p><strong>S1 - TS/JS artefact extraction succeeds</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 TypeScript file with class, constructor, method, interface, type, import, =
and function
When ingest runs
Then artefacts are created with correct canonical_kind and language_kind</p=
re>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S2 - Rust artefact extraction succeeds</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 Rust file with use, struct, trait, impl, method, and function
When ingest runs
Then artefacts are created and trait is normalized to canonical interface</=
pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S3 - Dependency edges are emitted</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given f=
iles with import/use and callable invocations
When ingest runs
Then imports, calls, references, extends, implements, and exports edges are=
 emitted with resolved or unresolved targets as applicable</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S4 - Local workspace changes update current state</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 previously indexed file in the workspace
When the file is edited locally
Then artefacts_current and artefact_edges_current are updated for that file=
 as a temporary revision</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S5 - Matching temporary current rows are promoted during ingest<=
/strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
emporary current rows produced from local workspace changes
And the blob for a file matches HEAD during ingest
When devql ingest runs
Then the matching current rows are marked as committed revision state
And file_state is updated for that commit/path/blob</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-7.2Alternativepaths">7.2 Alterna=
tive paths</h3>
<p><strong>S6 - Reverse dependency query</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given e=
xisting dependency edges
When query uses deps(kind:"calls", direction:"in")
Then callers of the selected symbol are returned</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S7 - Historical dependency query by commit</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given c=
ommitted historical rows exist for a commit
When query uses asOf(commit:"&lt;sha&gt;") and deps(...)
Then results are read from historical committed tables</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S8 - Temporary revision query</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 temporary workspace revision exists
When query uses asOf(saveRevision:"temp:&lt;id&gt;")
Then results are read from current tables filtered to that temporary revisi=
on</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-7.3Edgecases">7.3 Edge cases</h3=
>
<p><strong>E1 - Unresolved symbol fallback</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 call/import/reference that cannot resolve to a local artefact_id
When ingest runs
Then the edge stores to_symbol_ref and keeps the resolved artefact target n=
ull</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>E2 - Export and re-export dedup</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given r=
epeated export/re-export statements for the same normalized target
When ingest runs repeatedly
Then logical duplicate export edges are not duplicated</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>E3 - Symbol identity remains stable across line moves</strong></=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 symbol that moves lines without semantic change
When the file is re-indexed
Then symbol_id remains stable
And revision-specific artefact identity may still change with blob content<=
/pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>E4 - Deleted file clears current state</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 file currently represented in artefacts_current and artefact_edges_current
When the file is deleted from the workspace
Then the current rows for that path are removed</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>E5 - Macro invocation handling is conservative in V1</strong></p=
>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 Rust macro invocation
When dependency edges are emitted
Then any emitted macro call edge uses metadata call_form=3D"macro"
And unresolved macro calls may be omitted in V1 to avoid noisy fallback edg=
es</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-7.4Errorcases">7.4 Error cases</=
h3>
<p><strong>ERR1 - AST parse failure</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 syntactically invalid source file
When ingest runs
Then only file artefact is persisted for that file
And no symbol-level artefacts or edges are emitted for that file
And system logs parse failure details</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-8.Acceptancecriteria">8. Accepta=
nce criteria</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>S1 and S2 produce complete V1 artefacts with canonical mapping for abstr=
act kinds and <code>language_kind</code> fidelity for language-specific kin=
ds.</p></li>
<li>
<p>S3 produces V1 edge kinds: <code>imports</code>, <code>calls</code>, <co=
de>references</code>, <code>extends</code>, <code>implements</code>, <code>=
exports</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>S4 updates <code>artefacts_current</code> and <code>artefact_edges_curre=
nt</code> after local edits.</p></li>
<li>
<p>S5 promotes matching temporary current rows to committed current rows du=
ring ingest and updates <code>file_state</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>S6 returns correct incoming blast-radius dependencies.</p></li>
<li>
<p>S7 reads historical state through <code>asOf(commit/ref)</code>.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>S8 reads temporary workspace state through <code>asOf(saveRevision:...)<=
/code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>E1 persists unresolved targets through <code>to_symbol_ref</code> where =
fallback is supported.</p></li>
<li>
<p>E2 maintains deduped logical export edges across repeated ingest.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>E3 preserves <code>symbol_id</code> stability across non-semantic moves.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>E4 removes current-state rows for deleted files.</p></li>
<li>
<p>E5 uses <code>call_form=3D"macro"</code> for emitted macro edges and doe=
s not require unresolved macro fallback in V1.</p></li>
<li>
<p>ERR1 degrades safely to file-only artefact persistence.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Repeated ingest on unchanged inputs does not create duplicate logical ar=
tefacts or edges.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-9.APIcontracts">9. API contracts=
</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-9.1Querystagedefinitions">9.1 Qu=
ery stage definitions</h3>
<p><strong>Artefacts stage</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">artefac=
ts(kind:"function|method|interface|type|enum|variable|file|module|import", =
symbol_fqn:"...", lines:1..50)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Dependencies stage</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">deps(ki=
nd:"calls|imports|references|extends|implements|exports", direction:"out|in=
|both", include_unresolved:true|false)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Revision selector stage</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">asOf(co=
mmit:"&lt;sha&gt;")
asOf(ref:"main")
asOf(save:"current")
asOf(saveRevision:"temp:42")</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Compatibility note:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>inherits</code> is still accepted temporarily as a query alias and=
 is normalized internally to <code>extends</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Canonical output uses <code>extends</code> only.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-9.2Queryroutingsemantics">9.2 Qu=
ery routing semantics</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Query selector</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Artefact source</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Edge source</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No <code>asOf(...)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefacts_current</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefact_edges_current</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Latest current workspace state</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>asOf(save:"current")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefacts_current</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefact_edges_current</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Explicit current workspace state</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>asOf(saveRevision:"temp:&lt;id&gt;")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefacts_current</code> filtered by temporary revision</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefact_edges_current</code> filtered by temporary revision</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Specific temporary workspace revision</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>asOf(commit:"&lt;sha&gt;")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefacts</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefact_edges</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Historical committed state for a commit</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>asOf(ref:"main")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefacts</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>artefact_edges</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Historical committed state for a resolved ref</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-9.3Responserowfieldsfordeps(...)=
">9.3 Response row fields for <code>deps(...)</code></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "edge_id": "uuid",
  "edge_kind": "calls",
  "language": "typescript|javascript|rust",
  "from_artefact_id": "uuid",
  "to_artefact_id": "uuid|null",
  "to_symbol_ref": "string|null",
  "start_line": 12,
  "end_line": 12,
  "metadata": {}
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Error responses:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Validation error for unsupported stage combinations</p></li>
<li>
<p>Validation error for malformed args</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.Datamodelchanges">10. Data mo=
del changes</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.1Logicalstoragemodel">10.1 Lo=
gical storage model</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>artefacts</code>: committed historical artefacts keyed by revision=
-specific <code>artefact_id</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>artefact_edges</code>: committed historical edges keyed by <code>e=
dge_id</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>artefacts_current</code>: latest current symbol view keyed by <cod=
e>(repo_id, symbol_id)</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>artefact_edges_current</code>: latest current dependency view keye=
d by current edge natural uniqueness</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>file_state</code>: commit/path/blob mapping used for historical pa=
th resolution and promotion</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.2Revisionmetadataincurrent-st=
atetables">10.2 Revision metadata in current-state tables</h3>
<p><code>artefacts_current</code> and <code>artefact_edges_current</code> i=
nclude:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>commit_sha</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>revision_kind</code> (<code>commit</code> or <code>temporary</code=
>)</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>revision_id</code> (commit SHA or <code>temp:&lt;id&gt;</code>)</p=
></li>
<li>
<p><code>temp_checkpoint_id</code> when the row originated from a temporary=
 revision</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>updated_at</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.3Identitymodel">10.3 Identity=
 model</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>symbol_id</code> is the stable semantic identity for a symbol acro=
ss non-semantic line moves and formatting-only edits.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>artefact_id</code> is revision/blob-specific and may change when b=
lob content changes.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Current tables are keyed on stable symbol identity for efficient replace=
ment of the latest state.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Historical tables retain blob-scoped revision history.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.4Canonicaledgeanddependencyen=
ums">10.4 Canonical edge and dependency enums</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Ed=
geKind {
  imports,
  calls,
  references,
  extends,
  implements,
  exports
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum De=
psKind {
  imports,
  calls,
  references,
  extends,
  implements,
  exports
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum De=
psDirection {
  out,
  in,
  both
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>extends</code> is the canonical graph term.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Legacy <code>inherits</code> is accepted only as a temporary query alias=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Query results and stored new rows use <code>extends</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.5Depsmodel">10.5 Deps model</=
h3>
<p><code>deps(...)</code> is the query-layer projection over <code>artefact=
_edges</code> or <code>artefact_edges_current</code>, depending on the revi=
sion selector.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">type In=
cludeUnresolved =3D boolean;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">type De=
psQuery =3D {
  kind?: DepsKind;
  direction?: DepsDirection;
  include_unresolved?: IncludeUnresolved;
};</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">type De=
vqlDependencyEdgeRow =3D {
  edge_id: string;
  edge_kind: EdgeKind;
  language: "typescript" | "javascript" | "rust";
  from_artefact_id: string;
  to_artefact_id: string | null;
  to_symbol_ref: string | null;
  start_line: number | null;
  end_line: number | null;
  metadata: DevqlEdgeMetadata;
};</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Interpretation rules:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>kind</code> filters by <code>edge_kind</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>direction=3Dout</code> returns edges whose source is the selected =
artefact.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>direction=3Din</code> returns edges whose target resolves to the s=
elected artefact.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>direction=3Dboth</code> returns the union of <code>in</code> and <=
code>out</code> result sets.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>include_unresolved=3Dtrue</code> keeps rows where only <code>to_sy=
mbol_ref</code> is present.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>include_unresolved=3Dfalse</code> excludes unresolved edges from t=
he result set.</p></li>
<li>
<p>For <code>imports</code>, <code>exports</code>, and some unresolved or i=
mported calls, the target may be represented only by <code>to_symbol_ref</c=
ode>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>from_artefact_id</code> is always required.</p></li>
<li>
<p>At least one of <code>to_artefact_id</code> or <code>to_symbol_ref</code=
> must be present.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.6Edgemetadataenums">10.6 Edge=
 metadata enums</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Im=
portForm {
  binding,
  side_effect
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Re=
fKind {
  type,
  value
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Ca=
llForm {
  identifier,
  member,
  function,
  associated,
  method,
  macro
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Re=
solution {
  local,
  import,
  unresolved,
  re_export,
  external
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Ex=
portForm {
  declaration,
  default,
  named,
  re_export,
  re_export_all,
  re_export_namespace,
  pub_use
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.7Metadatashapebyedgekind">10.=
7 Metadata shape by edge kind</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">type De=
vqlEdgeMetadata =3D
  | { import_form: ImportForm }
  | { call_form: CallForm; resolution: Resolution }
  | { ref_kind: RefKind; resolution: Resolution }
  | {}
  | { export_name: string; export_form: ExportForm; resolution: Resolution =
};</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Edge kind to metadata mapping:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>imports</code> -&gt; <code>import_form</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>calls</code> -&gt; <code>call_form</code>, <code>resolution</code>=
</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>references</code> -&gt; <code>ref_kind</code>, <code>resolution</c=
ode></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>extends</code> -&gt; no metadata</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>implements</code> -&gt; no metadata</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>exports</code> -&gt; <code>export_name</code>, <code>export_form</=
code>, <code>resolution</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-10.8Artefacttaxonomyandmapping">=
10.8 Artefact taxonomy and mapping</h3>
<h4 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Canonicalartefactkinds(cross-lan=
guageabstractions)">Canonical artefact kinds (cross-language abstractions)<=
/h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>file</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>module</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>import</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>function</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>method</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>interface</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>type</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>enum</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>variable</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"ArtefactCompletionandBlastRadius-Language-specificartefactkinds(n=
ocanonicalinV1)">Language-specific artefact kinds (no canonical in V1)</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p>TypeScript/JavaScript: <code>class_declaration</code>, <code>constructor=
</code>, <code>property_declaration</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Rust: <code>impl_item</code>, <code>struct_item</code>, <code>const_item=
</code>, <code>static_item</code>, <code>macro_definition</code></p></li>
</ul>
